quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  10,43,"And of them are some who look at thee, so canst thou guide the blind, even though they see not"
  10,44,Verily Allah wrongeth not mankind in aught but mankind wrong themselves
  10,45,"And of the Day whereon He shall gather them, as though they had tarried not save an hour of he day they shall mutually recognize. Lost surely are those who belie the meeting with Allah and they were not such as to be guided"
  10,46,"And whether We shew thee soome of that which We have promised them, or We cause thee to die, Unto us is their return, and Allah is witness of that which they do"
  10,47,"And for each community there hath been sent an apostle; and when their apostle hath arrived, the matter between them is decreed in equity, and they are not wronged"
  10,48,"And they say: when cometh this promise, if ye say sooth"
  10,49,"Say thou: I own not any power of hurt or benefit unto myself, save that which Allah may will. For each community is a term; when their term hath arrived, not an hour can they stay behind nor can they advance"
  10,50,"Say thou: bethink ye, if His torment come on you by night or by day which Portion thereof would the culprlts hasten on"
  10,51,"Is It, then, when it hath befallen, that ye will believe therein Now?- whereas ye have surely been hastening it On"
  10,52,"Thereafter, it will be said unto those who wronged themselves: taste the torment everlasting: ye are requited not save for that which ye have been earning"
  10,53,"And they ask thee to tell them if it be-true. Say thou: yeal by my Lord, It, Is the veary truth, and ye shall not be able to escape"